@ Don_Alberto266

You can use Fraps to record the Desktop by going to the General page and selecting Monitor Aero Desktop (DWM). You will then see the yellow FPS overlay in the corner of your screen. Just press the key that you use to Record and you're recording.

Be aware, however, that it will occupy your CPU's resources extensively, so try not to have *too* going on. But it does work, nonetheless.
